    "description": "Mr. Graham entered the College Preparatory Department in the fall of 1899 and was graduated in the Agricultural Course with the degree of B. S. in 1907. He is thoroughly acquainted with every form of student life and has taken an active part in Y. M. C. A., literary, publication, athletic and dramatic work. As an instructor in agriculture, he is soon to take up work in Manila. During the past year Mr. Graham has been assistant in soil physics and has also been carrying on work for his M. S. degree in Agriculture. His M. S. work has been, \"A Detail Study of the Physical Properties of Soil from the Irrigation Plats of the College.\"",
    "image": "New Mexico State University_1908_页面_01.png"
  },
